          "content": "When global capital invests in a specific project, there are three reasons why it must route through an [[SPC|Special Purpose Company. A legal entity established solely for one project. Completely separates assets from parent company debt, litigation, and bankruptcy.]] rather than investing directly: ① Asset separation (blocking parent company risk), ② Tax optimization (utilizing tax treaties), ③ Capital structure simplification (organizing multinational investors).",
