          "title": "5. Why Structural Designers Think About Exit First",
          "content": "A financial designer is not someone who designs the investment entry — they design the exit in reverse, working backward.",
          "closing": "Those who design money with structure do not add exit strategy at the end. They define the exit first, then design all structures in reverse toward that exit. This is the essence of financial structure design.",
