              "character": "Kim Joon-hyuk · Yeongdo, Busan",
              "text": "Joon-hyuk returned to Yeongdo.\n\nThe Hanyang Shipping headquarters building had already been sold. A convenience store had moved into the first floor.\n\nHe climbed the third-floor stairs. An empty office with no one inside. Where his father's desk had been. Now an empty space.\n\nHe sat on the floor. Pulled a book from his bag.\n\nThe book his father had hidden away.\n『Those Who Design Money with Structure』\n\nInside the front cover, in his father's handwriting:\n\n'Joon-hyuk, money is not earned. It is designed.'\n\nHe finally understood.\n\nHis father had never been able to design. He knew the concept but lacked the language.\n\nAnd he — had learned the language.\n\nNot because he was smarter than his father.\nBecause his father's failure had been his textbook.\n\nHe stood up.\n\nThe next structure was already taking shape in his head."
